This brand-new Flex Industrial development in Southwest Austin offers modern, versatile spaces designed to accommodate a wide range of business needs. OWN INSTEAD OF RENT

Owning your commercial space isn’t just a smart operational decision, it’s a strategic financial move. With the continued rise in rental rates and limited inventory in prime locations, now is the ideal time to invest in your business and secure a real estate asset that works for you.

This Flex Industrial development is ideal for owner-users, investors, and businesses seeking a functional, upscale space in a prime Austin-area location. With demand surging and limited inventory in the region, these new construction suites represent a compelling opportunity for growth-minded buyers.

Why Own Your Commercial Space Instead of Leasing?
When it comes to your business, your commercial space should be more than just a place to operate — it should be an investment in your future. Just like a residential home or office building, owning your business property allows you to build long-term equity and benefit from appreciation over time.

Each unit in this Flex Industrial development is part of a commercial condominium regime, meaning you own your space and receive a deed at closing—just like a traditional real estate transaction. Shared amenities are professionally managed through a monthly owners' association (similar to an HOA), ensuring a clean, well-maintained environment that retains value over time.

Advantages of Owning vs. Leasing:
Build Equity, Not Just Rent Receipts
Monthly lease payments are an expense that disappear with time. Owning your space means every payment builds your equity and wealth.

Lock In Your Monthly Costs
Avoid unpredictable rent hikes and enjoy long-term financial stability with low, fixed monthly payments.

Tax Advantages
If the property is used for business purposes, you may deduct interest expenses and benefit from depreciation—providing meaningful reductions in your annual income tax liability.

Appreciation & Exit Value
As the market grows, so does your investment. Capture property appreciation and potentially realize a profit at the time of resale.

Custom Control Over Your Space
Enjoy full autonomy over design and layout. Plus, your investments in upgrades and improvements add to your asset's value, rather than being lost in a leased space.

Inflation Protection
With a fixed mortgage or payment structure, you’re naturally hedged against inflation while leasing costs continue to climb.

Professional Ownership Structure
Ownership through a condominium regime means shared costs for maintenance and upkeep—delivering long-term value and hassle-free ownership.

Bottom Line:
Owning your commercial space isn’t just a smart operational decision—it’s a strategic financial move. With the continued rise in rental rates and limited inventory in prime locations, now is the ideal time to invest in your business and secure a real estate asset that works for you.

description:
Versatile mixed-use commercial property zoned CS-MU-V-CO-NP offering a flexible live/work layout on vibrant North Lamar Boulevard. Positioned along a key connector between IH-35 and Mopac Expy, this stand-alone building captures excellent drive-by exposure with prominent front display windows and strong traffic counts. The main level offers an updated retail space plus and storage room, while the upstairs apartment includes a full kitchen, bath/shower, closets, and private deck. Currently leased, it generates immediate income.
Exterior features include 4 paved parking spaces, ample street parking, and a 30 ft pole sign with a 6 ft x 8 ft lighted sign box with proper permitting. Recent upgrades include electrical, plumbing, flooring, and bathroom improvements, along with a freshly painted exterior.
Walkable to CapMetro light rail, neighborhood restaurants, and daily conveniences, with quick access to The Domain, Q2 Stadium, W Anderson Ln, Burnet Road, Highway 183, and downtown Austin. Just blocks from the soon to be redeveloped Anderson Square that will bring potentially thousands of additional housing units to the area.

brokerDetails.name: Jason Steinberg
brokerDetails.tagLine: Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects.
brokerDetails.bio:
Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects. Jason has provided leasing and sales services since 2008 and prior to joining ECR in 2010, Jason worked at a local commercial construction firm.

Jason has successfully completed more than 1,100 real estate deals totaling more than $1,000,000,000 in value. He is annually recognized as an Austin Business Journal “Heavy Hitter” and received the SIOR Designation in 2016.

Jason is involved with the Society of Industrial and Office Realtors (SIOR), the Commercial Brokers Association (CBA), Austin Diaper Bank, Sammy’s House, the Anti-Defamation League (ADL), and the Jewish Community Association of Austin.

Jason received a B.A. degree from The University of Texas at Austin. Jason and his wife, Allison, have two young children and live in Austin’s Northwest Hills neighborhood.

brokerDetails.name: David Dawkins
brokerDetails.tagLine: David is known for his attention to detail, integrity, creative problem-solving skills, and his commitment to exceeding client expectations
brokerDetails.bio:
David is known for his attention to detail, integrity, creative problem-solving skills, and his commitment to exceeding client expectations. He rejoined ECR in 2019 to help continue building their tenant and buyer representation practices. David has focused on the Austin office market for 15+ years, bringing in-depth knowledge and expertise to the team. To ensure each client reaches the optimum solution for their real estate requirements, David combines an in-depth analysis of each client’s business objectives and facility requirements with market knowledge, financial analysis, and intensive negotiation skills.

David holds an M.B.A from St. Edward’s University and a B.S. in Communications from the University of Texas at Austin. He is a proud parent of two boys, a member of St. John Neumann Catholic Church, and an avid mountain biker, runner, hunter, and fisher.

brokerDetails.name: Connor Atchley
brokerDetails.tagLine: Connor currently oversees a leasing portfolio totaling over 1.2 million square feet on behalf of his clients
brokerDetails.bio: Connor Atchley joined Stream Realty Partners in 2013 and serves as a Vice President within the firm’s office team in Austin. His primary responsibilities include marketing and leasing commercial properties, as well as sourcing strategic investment opportunities for his clients. Connor currently oversees a leasing portfolio totaling over 1.2 million square feet on behalf of his clients, which include and have included: KBS, CIM, USAA Real Co, AFIAA, MIG, Dividend Capital, Heitman, and DRA Advisors. Prior to joining Stream Realty Partners, Connor played professional basketball in Turkey and the United States before returning to his alma mater to receive a masters in Advertising. While attending The University of Texas he worked for the UT Men’s basketball team as a graduate assistant.

brokerDetails.name: Carly Langley
brokerDetails.bio: With more than a decade of experience partnering with some of the industry’s most forward-thinking companies, Langley will play a pivotal role in advancing Transwestern’s business development initiatives. Her experience includes launching the first WeWork locations in Texas and the southern U.S., leading regional sales for a top hospitality firm, and overseeing business development for one of Austin’s largest owner-developers.

brokerDetails.name: Brandon Lester
brokerDetails.bio: Brandon joined Transwestern in 2006. He specializes on agency leasing, life science and healthcare advisory services for institutional and private clients. Brandon has built strong relationships and earned the trust of regional and national clients including Ascension Seton, Welltower, Healthpeak Medical Office Properties, Olympus Ventures, Clarion Partners, Barings, Wedge Holdings, Omnient Capital, as well as many local and regional clients. Brandon is the recipient for several awards, both regionally and nationally, for his accomplishments at Transwestern. In 2017 Brandon was part of the Austin healthcare advisory team receiving Transwestern’s National Tenant Advisory Deal of the Year. In recognition of Brandon’s leasing transaction volume in 2011 he received Transwestern’s  National Young Gun Award. Transwestern’s Central Texas Legendary Service Award was awarded to Brandon in 2007 in acknowledgement of his extraordinary client service. Brandon has ranked in Austin Business Journal’s 25 top ’Heavy Hitters in Real Estate’ since 2008 and has been recognized as a CoStar Power Broker since 2009.

brokerDetails.name: Helen Jobes, CCIM
brokerDetails.tagLine: Helen Jobes specializes in the sale and leasing of office, retail, and industrial properties, as well as investment sales.
brokerDetails.bio:
Helen Jobes, CCIM, specializes in the sale and leasing of office, retail, and industrial property as well as investment sales in Central Texas, San Antonio, Houston and the Rio Grande Valley. During her 40-year career, Jobes has leased over 1,000,000 square feet of office space and sold more than 5.1 million square feet of commercial real estate, including office, office/warehouse projects, apartments, retail centers and land. Though skilled in all property types, Jobes focuses primarily on office investments and leasing.

Jobes served as the investment sales broker at Trammell Crow (now CBRE) and is principal and founder of Gold Eagle Investments since 2002.

Jobes served on the Board of Directors for the Real Estate Council of Austin for eleven years, which is a 2,300 member organization comprised of business and real estate professionals. She is currently a member and has also served on the Board and as past president of the Austin Commercial Real Estate Society. She is a member of the Central Texas Commercial Brokers Association and CCIM Institute. She is also a member of the Urban Land Institute and served on the Austin Board of ULI for 3 years.

In 2009, Jobes was introduced to the China Real Estate Chamber of Commerce (CRECC) and along with the Mayor of Austin, the Chamber of Commerce and Opportunity Austin hosted a delegation of 30 Chinese investors who came to the United States to learn about investing in commercial real estate. In 2010, Jobes was a guest speaker at the 2010 International Forum of 50+ Communities held in Sanya, Hainan, China. Helen Jobes has represented such clients as PM Realty Advisors, Lowe Enterprises, R.M. Crowe Company, Harvard Properties Trust, Morrison Karsten Group, Triple Net Properties, First National Bank, C.W. Dalcan, MFB Real Estate, John Crutchfield, Sandy Gottesman, Rick Hardin, Chi Kao Hsu, Harren Interests, John Graham, Cheryl Ogle, Stadler Investments, Texas Public Employees Association, BCumby Investments, Dawlette Companies, High Street Retail, Kennedy Wilson, Oakpoint Properties, Synermark Properties,  Austin Telco Federal Credit Union, Byram Properties and AP Equity Properties, LTD.

Jobes has been involved with the Boys and Girls Club for the past 18 years and served as the first woman President of the Boys and Girls Club Foundation in 2017. She attended UT/RGV, the University of Texas and St. Edward's University.

brokerDetails.name: John Jobes
brokerDetails.tagLine: John Jobes is a high achieving and dedicated commercial real estate agent.

brokerDetails.name: Darryl Dadon
brokerDetails.tagLine: Specializing in institutional landlord representation and corporate tenant representation across the Austin market
brokerDetails.bio: Darryl Dadon is a Senior Vice President with CBRE's Austin office. He specializes in institutional landlord representation and corporate tenant representation across the Austin market, and engages in a variety of projects, including investment sales, dispositions, and industrial and office/flex leasing assignments. Devoted to his team’s success, Darryl actively markets properties, prepares financial lease analysis, performs strategic lease negotiations, and executes a broad range of transactional activities for a diversified set of institution owners. For IndCor Properties, a 3.75 million square foot flex portfolio, his team increased rental rates 25% and moved occupancy from 89% to 99% within a 10-month period. In recent years, Trammell Crow Company and Clarion Partners retained his team to lease 450k square feet at Expo Business Park. His team handles a portfolio in excess of 6 million square feet of office and flex properties and over 6 million square feet of developable office buildings in the Austin market, and his work continues to advance the team’s growing portfolio in the Greater Austin area. Darryl began his career in multifamily commercial real estate with Sperry Van Ness Commercial Realty where he successfully marketed and sold San Diego commercial real estate and maximized returns in a limited time frame. Through galvanized marketing efforts, he increased monthly client contact tenfold. After gaining specialized multifamily experience, Darryl transitioned to residential real estate for Pacific Sotheby’s International Realty, specializing in investment sales of luxury residential homes. He provided his clients a mastered marketing strategy, as well as a results-driven process, that delivered success.

brokerDetails.name: Olivia Reed
brokerDetails.tagLine: Leasing and Tenant Representation.
brokerDetails.bio: Olivia Reed assists with Industrial transactions with Darryl Dadon in Austin, TX. For the past six years, Ms. Reed has gained knowledge in tenant representation, leasing, sales, land, and assisting Fortune 500 companies on a local and national level. She has assisted on over 25 million square feet of transactions since she began her career at CBRE in 2016. Relocated from now CBRE Headquarters in Dallas, TX, she brings clients in Austin strategic thinking and creativity in marketing, reporting, business development, and more.

brokerDetails.name: Katie Ekstrom
brokerDetails.bio: Katie is a Senior Vice President in the CBRE Austin office, specializing in project leasing and business development with the Office Leasing Advisory Services division. She has over 17 years of commercial real estate experience. Katie’s scope of responsibilities include: negotiations encompassing all stages of the commercial transaction, identifying and accurately reporting market conditions, strategic client consulting, new business pursuits and securing current and future client relationships. Before relocating to Austin more than ten years ago and joining the Office Leasing Advisory team at CBRE, Katie was a leasing broker with Transwestern in Houston, Texas where she oversaw an office portfolio of approximately 2.5 million square feet in several major submarkets. Since 2005, Katie has completed over 700 lease transactions, representing over 4.5 million rentable square feet. With her strong leadership both within the community and the commercial real estate community, Ms. Ekstrom has been recognized as a Heavy Hitter in the Austin Business Journal multiple years.

brokerDetails.name: Clark Jones
brokerDetails.tagLine: Leasing and Development Representative at Brandywine Realty Trust.
brokerDetails.bio: Clark Jones currently works as a Leasing and Development Representative for Brandywine Realty Trust based in Austin, Texas. Prior to this role, Clark worked in Lincoln Property Company's Corporate Services Group, Data Center Solutions for Lincoln Rackhouse, and Tenant Advisory Services for Transwestern.

brokerDetails.name: Joseph Caperton
brokerDetails.tagLine: Mr. Caperton is the Vice President of Leasing for Brandywine's Richmond Office.
brokerDetails.bio: Mr. Caperton joined Brandywine in 1999 and currently serves as Senior Vice President of Leasing, with responsibility for the leasing and development of the Company’s Richmond, Metro DC, and Austin portfolios.  Mr. Caperton has negotiated the vast majority of the office portfolio leases for the Company’s Richmond Region since he joined the Company.  He is a member of the Greater Richmond Association for Commercial Real Estate (GRACRE).

brokerDetails.name: Troy Holme
brokerDetails.bio: Troy Holme is a Vice Chairman focused on office leasing, transaction management, and new business pursuits for the Austin office of CBRE. During his 16 years at CBRE, Mr. Holme has been actively involved in the creation and implementation of marketing strategies to provide solutions for clients, with his main focus on leasing office product in Austin, TX. Mr. Holme and his office team are responsible for formulating and successfully executing strategies for marketing, leasing, acquisitions/dispositions, and asset advisory on a 30-building, 5-million square foot Austin portfolio. Mr. Holme previously worked for Arden Realty, Inc., where he oversaw leasing and asset management of 6-million square feet of office buildings valued at more that $4 billion in the Los Angeles area. During the course of his career, Mr. Holme has signed thousands of lease transactions and sold multiple office buildings totaling well over $5 billion in value.

brokerDetails.name: Casey Ford
brokerDetails.bio: Casey Ford is a Executive Vice President in CBRE's Austin office and specializes in office leasing and sale transactions. Throughout his career, Casey has completed more than 850 sale and lease transactions, compromising over 5.5 million square feet with a total valuation of approximately $2 billion. Casey has been fortunate to work with many of the most respected ownership groups in the country including Invesco, Principal Real Estate Investors, CBRE Global Investors, Metropolitan Life Insurance Company, Brandywine, Menlo Equities, and Trammell Crow Company. Casey began his career with CBRE in San Diego in 2000, where he was a participant in CBRE's Wheel Program. After spending more than five years in San Diego, Casey relocated to the Austin office where he has focused on the office market since the end of 2005.

brokerDetails.name: Adam Green, SIOR
brokerDetails.tagLine: Austin market expert. President of Lee & Associates Austin
brokerDetails.bio:
Born and raised in Austin, Adam brings over a decade of expertise in commercial real estate to his role as President of Lee & Associates - Austin. During his nearly 12 years at Stream Realty Partners, Adam established himself as Austin’s leading industrial real estate broker, completing over 700 transactions totaling more than $1.5 billion in consideration. 
  
As the founder of Lee & Associates’ Austin office, Adam leads a full-service brokerage team specializing in industrial, land, office, retail, and multifamily real estate. His team provides comprehensive services, including leasing, tenant representation, acquisitions, dispositions, and development consulting, to help clients navigate Austin’s rapidly evolving market. 
  
Known for its entrepreneurial spirit and broker-owned model, Lee & Associates is the largest broker-owned commercial real estate firm in North America, with over 75 offices and 1,600 professionals completing more than $115 billion in transaction volume over the past five years. By aligning with Lee & Associates, Adam combines his local market expertise with the resources of a nationally recognized firm to deliver exceptional value to his clients. 
  
Austin, as the epicenter of innovation in the U.S., continues to experience rapid growth, and Adam is committed to helping owners and occupiers thrive in this dynamic environment. Under his leadership, Lee & Associates Austin is actively expanding its team and capabilities to meet the demands of this fast-paced market.

brokerDetails.name: Michael Smith
brokerDetails.bio: Michael joins Lee & Associates as Vice President, bringing a strong background in industrial, retail, and land transactions. He specializes in project leasing, tenant representation, acquisitions, and dispositions across Central Texas.

brokerDetails.name: Avery Levy
brokerDetails.bio:
Avery Levy is a senior at the University of Texas at Austin studying economics with a minor in real estate. He started working in real estate his freshmen year at UT Austin and will continue to hone his expertise in the Austin market.

Avery also serves on the executive board of the Texas Silver Spurs, an honorary service organization at UT Austin, and will continue his dedication to service in Austin after graduation.

With a passion for real estate and commitment to excellence, Avery brings energy, focus and a collaborative spirit to every opportunity.

brokerDetails.tagLine: Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects.
brokerDetails.bio:
Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects. Jason has provided leasing and sales services since 2008 and prior to joining ECR in 2010, Jason worked at a local commercial construction firm.

Jason has successfully completed more than 1,100 real estate deals totaling more than $1,000,000,000 in value. He is annually recognized as an Austin Business Journal “Heavy Hitter” and received the SIOR Designation in 2016.

Jason is involved with the Society of Industrial and Office Realtors (SIOR), the Commercial Brokers Association (CBA), Austin Diaper Bank, Sammy’s House, the Anti-Defamation League (ADL), and the Jewish Community Association of Austin.

Jason received a B.A. degree from The University of Texas at Austin. Jason and his wife, Allison, have two young children and live in Austin’s Northwest Hills neighborhood.

brokerDetails.name: Darryl Dadon
brokerDetails.tagLine: Specializing in institutional landlord representation and corporate tenant representation across the Austin market
brokerDetails.bio: Darryl Dadon is a Senior Vice President with CBRE's Austin office. He specializes in institutional landlord representation and corporate tenant representation across the Austin market, and engages in a variety of projects, including investment sales, dispositions, and industrial and office/flex leasing assignments. Devoted to his team’s success, Darryl actively markets properties, prepares financial lease analysis, performs strategic lease negotiations, and executes a broad range of transactional activities for a diversified set of institution owners. For IndCor Properties, a 3.75 million square foot flex portfolio, his team increased rental rates 25% and moved occupancy from 89% to 99% within a 10-month period. In recent years, Trammell Crow Company and Clarion Partners retained his team to lease 450k square feet at Expo Business Park. His team handles a portfolio in excess of 6 million square feet of office and flex properties and over 6 million square feet of developable office buildings in the Austin market, and his work continues to advance the team’s growing portfolio in the Greater Austin area. Darryl began his career in multifamily commercial real estate with Sperry Van Ness Commercial Realty where he successfully marketed and sold San Diego commercial real estate and maximized returns in a limited time frame. Through galvanized marketing efforts, he increased monthly client contact tenfold. After gaining specialized multifamily experience, Darryl transitioned to residential real estate for Pacific Sotheby’s International Realty, specializing in investment sales of luxury residential homes. He provided his clients a mastered marketing strategy, as well as a results-driven process, that delivered success.

brokerDetails.name: Olivia Reed
brokerDetails.tagLine: Leasing and Tenant Representation.
brokerDetails.bio: Olivia Reed assists with Industrial transactions with Darryl Dadon in Austin, TX. For the past six years, Ms. Reed has gained knowledge in tenant representation, leasing, sales, land, and assisting Fortune 500 companies on a local and national level. She has assisted on over 25 million square feet of transactions since she began her career at CBRE in 2016. Relocated from now CBRE Headquarters in Dallas, TX, she brings clients in Austin strategic thinking and creativity in marketing, reporting, business development, and more.

brokerDetails.name: Blake Patterson
brokerDetails.bio:
Blake is well established and highly regarded in the Austin industrial real estate industry. His longstanding tenure and knowledge of the Austin market enable him to provide his clients with best-in-class service and superior market knowledge.
Blake is an expert in all things industrial, including tenant representation, project leasing and asset acquisitions & dispositions. His experience is as broad as it is deep; Blake has worked with other national and regional powerhouses prior to joining AQUILA, including HPI and CBRE. Living up to Austin’s reputation as the nation’s live music capital, Blake is also an accomplished singer-songwriter and can often be found performing live at one of the city’s many music venues.

brokerDetails.name: Jon Moscoe
brokerDetails.tagLine: Specializes in office and retail leasing, acquisition, and disposition transactions
brokerDetails.bio:
Jon Moscoe is the Vice President of Live Oak’s Office & Retail Divisions. He focuses on project lease negotiations, tenant representation, acquisitions, dispositions, site development, and marketing operations on behalf of Live Oak and its clients.

Since joining Live Oak in 2012, Jon has completed well over 400 transactions totaling more than 2.5 million square feet. He manages a diverse portfolio that has included institutional clients such as Clarion Partners, Lionstone, and TA Realty.

He has been recognized as a “Commercial Real Estate Heavy Hitter” by the Austin Business Journal for multiple years. Jon was born and raised in Austin.

brokerDetails.name: Brian Liverman
brokerDetails.bio: A native of Austin, Texas, Brian joined Cushman & Wakefield through the acquisition of Peloton Commercial Real Estate. He co-founded the Austin office of Peloton in 2013, alongside Matt Frizzell and Kevin Granger. With nearly 20 years’ experience, Brian’s primary focus is office leasing. He also has a hand in all aspects of the industry including development, tenant representation and acquisition/disposition services. Over the past decade he has been involved with the acquisition/disposition of over 2 million square feet of office and industrial space. Throughout his career, Brian has held positions as a Vice President with Stream Realty Partners, the Director of Leasing with Live Oak-Gottesman and a Vice President and department head with Trammell Crow Company. Consistently a top producer in the industry, Brian has been honored numerous times by the Austin Business Journal and others throughout his career.

brokerDetails.name: Matt Frizzell
brokerDetails.tagLine: Executive Director for Cushman & Wakefield focusing on office project leasing and landlord representation.
brokerDetails.bio: Matt joined Cushman and Wakefield in 2019 after selling Peloton Commercial Real Estate. Matt was one of Peloton Austin’s founding partners, alongside Kevin Granger and Brian Liverman. His primary focus is representing landlords on property leasing and management as well as investment sales and tenant representation. Matt’s experience in consulting real estate investors throughout the years in the underwriting process gives him a unique understanding of value creation on every type of asset. Prior to forming Peloton Austin, Matt was a Vice President with Stream Realty Partners. During his tenure at Stream, Matt completed transactions in excess of 4 million square feet. He has consistently been a top producer and has received numerous awards and recognition for his work throughout his career.

brokerDetails.name: John Cummings
brokerDetails.tagLine: Director of Marketing
brokerDetails.bio: John was born and raised in Austin, Texas and graduated Westlake High School in 2011. Succeeding his education at Westlake, John was accepted into the Leeds School of Business at the University of Colorado at Boulder. While studying in Colorado, he discovered his passion for marketing and real estate.  In May 2015, John graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration with an emphasis in Marketing.  In June 2015, he accepted his position as Director of Marketing and Sales with Quest Realty Inc.  Since obtaining his license in October 2015, John has assisted in the sale and acquisition of over $4,000,000 worth of office condominiums and retail projects. John specializes in marketing, tenant representation and property sales in his role with Quest Realty and is a member of the Texas Association of Realtors and the Austin Board of Realtors.

brokerDetails.name: Darryl Dadon
brokerDetails.tagLine: Specializing in institutional landlord representation and corporate tenant representation across the Austin market
brokerDetails.bio: Darryl Dadon is a Senior Vice President with CBRE's Austin office. He specializes in institutional landlord representation and corporate tenant representation across the Austin market, and engages in a variety of projects, including investment sales, dispositions, and industrial and office/flex leasing assignments. Devoted to his team’s success, Darryl actively markets properties, prepares financial lease analysis, performs strategic lease negotiations, and executes a broad range of transactional activities for a diversified set of institution owners. For IndCor Properties, a 3.75 million square foot flex portfolio, his team increased rental rates 25% and moved occupancy from 89% to 99% within a 10-month period. In recent years, Trammell Crow Company and Clarion Partners retained his team to lease 450k square feet at Expo Business Park. His team handles a portfolio in excess of 6 million square feet of office and flex properties and over 6 million square feet of developable office buildings in the Austin market, and his work continues to advance the team’s growing portfolio in the Greater Austin area. Darryl began his career in multifamily commercial real estate with Sperry Van Ness Commercial Realty where he successfully marketed and sold San Diego commercial real estate and maximized returns in a limited time frame. Through galvanized marketing efforts, he increased monthly client contact tenfold. After gaining specialized multifamily experience, Darryl transitioned to residential real estate for Pacific Sotheby’s International Realty, specializing in investment sales of luxury residential homes. He provided his clients a mastered marketing strategy, as well as a results-driven process, that delivered success.

brokerDetails.name: Olivia Reed
brokerDetails.tagLine: Leasing and Tenant Representation.
brokerDetails.bio: Olivia Reed assists with Industrial transactions with Darryl Dadon in Austin, TX. For the past six years, Ms. Reed has gained knowledge in tenant representation, leasing, sales, land, and assisting Fortune 500 companies on a local and national level. She has assisted on over 25 million square feet of transactions since she began her career at CBRE in 2016. Relocated from now CBRE Headquarters in Dallas, TX, she brings clients in Austin strategic thinking and creativity in marketing, reporting, business development, and more.

description:
4611 E MLK Blvd is a free standing 2,012 SF Convenience Store with four gas pumps. The recently redeveloped building sits on 0.40 acres on a hard corner of the highly visible intersection of Springdale and East Martin Luther King Jr Blvd with high-traffic counts along one of East Austin’s busiest intersections.
This offering is ideal for an investor seeking long-term stability: the transaction is structured as a 15-year sale-leaseback. The property was redeveloped in 2019 with the building being completely new, existing foundation repaired and tied into a new foundation to expand the C-Store’s footprint.  An investor will be purchasing a fully leased, creditworthy tenant, securing steady cash flow from a well-located property with high upside.
This Chevron sits on one of the most accessible corners in Austin. The C-store sits a mere 2 minutes from Hwy 183, 7 minutes from the high-density development Mueller and close by to Airport Blvd, Hwy I-35, Hwy 290 and Austin-Bergstrom International Airport. The area has been absorbing significant investment in retail, multifamily, and other commercial projects, and consumer activity is increasing because of it. An investor will likely reap the benefits of a strong uptick in residents and regional commuters. All this combined makes this a very attractive asset for someone looking for reliable returns and long-term upside.

description:
: DWG Capital Group is selling the two-building 10,500SF property for the price of $2,506,400 at an attractive land basis of$55.90 PSF and the building for $238 PSF. The site is located just 10miles from Downtown Austin, Texas and is in a thriving industrial market.Building A was constructed in 1984 and totals 7,500 SF; Building B wasbuilt in 1992 and totals 3,000 SF.THE LOCATION: Austin Iron is ally located in a highly trafficked business park right off Highway 290, providing easy access throughout the metro. It is situated in East Austin in the Dafffin/University Hills/Manor areas in thriving Travis County. Austin has recently exploded into the fastest-growing major metro in the United States over the last decade, per the U.S. Census Bureau. As major companies like Tesla continue relocating from California to Central Texas, Austin's rapid population growth shows no signs of stopping. Not only is Austin the number one job market, but it is also one of the hottest industrial markets in Texas and nationwide.
INvESTMENT SUMMARY
Purchase Price: $2,506,400 (6% Cap) NOI: $150,384 Base Rental Rate PSF: $13.90 PSF Purchase Price PSF: $238 Approximate Bldg SF: 10,500 SF Land Acres: Approx. 1.0 AC Rent Escalations: 3% Lease Terms: 5 years (3 yrs + two 1 yr extensions) Initial Lease Term: Start: 06/01/2024 End: 05/31/2029 Tenant: Austin Iron
Property Type: Industrial
"The Austin industrial market continues to break records and attract major players, with
net absorption reaching 2.5 million sq. ft. in Q1 2024, led by industry giants SpaceX and
Tesla occupying state-of-the-art build-to-suit facilities, alongside strong demand from
Tesla suppliers leasing speculative space. New construction surged, delivering 3.1 million
sq. ft., with nearly 50% pre-leased – a testament to the market's strength. Asking rents
climbed steadily, hitting $13.29 PSF market-wide, while in premium new buildings, rents
surged to as high as $20 PSF, reflecting the value placed on Austin’s modern,
strategically located industrial facilities. With robust leasing, record-breaking deliveries,
and unwavering tenant demand, Austin solidifies its position as one of the fastest-
growing and most dynamic industrial markets in the nation.
”
(Sources: CBRE, JLL)
NEW LEASE RENTAL RATE: The new 5-year lease features a 3-year primary term and two 1-year options, with attractive 3% annual rent increases. The annual rent is $150,384, or
$13.90 per square foot (PSF). The strength of the lease, tenant, and location makes the Austin Iron sale-leaseback an ideal acquisition opportunity, offering hands-off, stabilized revenue streams in a top 5 U.S. growth market. STABILIZED INCOME WITH SUPERIOR RENT GROWTH AND EXCALATIONS: This strategic opportunity provides a simple path
to success and profit. A new purchaser can acquire the cash flow from the current location and benefit from strong future profits in a market with trending rental rates of
approximately $15-$20 PSF NNN in this rapidly growing, best-in-Texas industrial market.
TENANCY: DESIGN. DRAW. FABRICATE AND INSTALL. Austin Iron, a strong, high-growth tenant, is an ironworks design, fabrication, and installation company benefiting from high demand in Austin's booming construction economy. The tenant has occupied the location since 2014, experiencing consistent year-over-year growth and maintaining many
months of backlogged demand. This seasoned tenant recently executed a 5-year NNN lease, structured as a 3-year base term with two 1-year extensions. Annual sales remain robust, and the new lease, while slightly below market, includes attractive 3% annual escalations, aligning well with the thriving, high-demand East Austin industrial market.

description: Discover a rare opportunity to own a piece of South Austin history on Appaloosa Run — a sprawling 27+/- acre property that perfectly blends rich heritage with incredible development potential. Once part of the original Koenig Ranch established in 1921, this land carries the spirit of the Texas pioneer days while offering all the modern advantages of city water and unrestricted use. The gently rolling terrain makes for an ideal canvas to bring your vision to life, whether you imagine a residential community, a private estate, or a boutique development that honors the property’s historic roots. Scattered across the acreage, you’ll find majestic heritage oak trees, long-distance Hill Country views, and multiple picturesque old barns that tell stories of generations past. Adding to the property’s timeless charm is a 1870-built farmhouse, accompanied by a quaint guest house — both of which could be thoughtfully incorporated into your future plans as a sales office, community center, or centerpiece of a heritage-inspired project. Located a short drive from downtown Austin with quick access to FM 1826 and SH 45, this is one of the last large remaining tracts in the area — a truly exceptional setting that combines convenience, history, and natural beauty. An additional 3 acres is also available adjacent to the property, allowing even greater flexibility and scale for your vision. With its storied past, easy build sites, and unmatched location, this property offers a once-in-a-lifetime chance to shape the next chapter of South Austin’s landscape.

description: Turnkey, Fully Rebuilt Quadplex in East Austin — Zero Permitting Headaches, Immediate Cash Flow Potential! 6709 Wentworth Drive presents a rare opportunity to acquire a completely rebuilt four-plex in one of Austin’s most dynamic submarkets. Following a fire several years ago, the property was reconstructed from the ground up, offering investors a true new-construction asset without the long and costly permitting process typical of City of Austin projects. Each unit features modern interiors with granite countertops, gas ranges, quality cabinetry, and designer finishes, creating long-term tenant appeal and minimal maintenance needs. With brand-new electrical, plumbing, HVAC, roofing, and structure, investors can expect years of worry-free performance and predictable operating expenses. Located at the front of the neighborhood just off Loyola Drive, residents enjoy quick access to Mueller, downtown Austin, and major employers, while the property’s fenced parking lot, shared front yards, and individual private backyards provide both convenience and privacy. This is the ideal addition to any portfolio seeking a stabilized, high-quality multifamily investment in a strong rental corridor with continued appreciation potential. Each unit features a fireplace, 2 bedrooms and 1 1/2 bathrooms.

description:
Austin’s Next Growth Corner — 24± Acres at FM 973 & SH 130

Prime Dual-Frontage Development Opportunity | Austin ETJ | No Zoning

Positioned at the high-exposure intersection of FM 973 and SH 130, this 24± acre corner tract represents one of the last major development sites within Austin’s rapidly expanding SH 130 corridor.  With dual frontage along both FM 973 and the SH 130 frontage road, the property offers exceptional visibility, access, and flexibility.

Located in the Austin ETJ with no zoning restrictions, the site supports a wide range of potential uses including industrial, commercial, retail, office, multifamily, residential or mixed-use development. Its flat, build-ready topography and available utilities make it ideal for immediate or phased development.

The property includes a move-in-ready office/retail building with three private offices, conference room, kitchen, open bullpen, and two restrooms providing interim income potential while entitlements or design planning are underway.  A fenced yard, storage shed, and gated entry offer additional usability for contractor, fleet, or yard operations.  Three existing tenants with short term leases provide additional income, helping offset holding costs while maintaining flexibility for future redevelopment.

Strategically located with immediate access to SH 130, FM 973, US 290, SH 71, and IH-35, the site connects directly to Austin’s key industrial and logistics corridors. Major employers nearby include Tesla (10 min), Austin-Bergstrom International Airport (15 min), Samsung Taylor (25 min), and Downtown Austin (20 min).

Highlights:

±24 Acres | Dual Frontage on FM 973 & SH 130

High-traffic interchange corner (25,000+ VPD combined)

No Zoning – Austin ETJ | Unlimited Development Flexibility

Existing Office/Retail Building – Ready for occupancy or lease

Fenced Yard + Storage Shed | Ideal for interim use income

Flat, Developable Terrain | Utilities available/nearby

Proximity to Tesla, Samsung, ABIA, and major logistics hubs

Investment Summary:
A rare large-scale corner tract offering income today and development upside tomorrow in one of Central Texas’s fastest-growing corridors. Perfect for industrial, flex, retail, or mixed-use projects benefiting from SH 130’s continued growth and accessibility.

description: Prime downtown Austin mixed-use 11,776 SF development parcel (Lots 7 & 8 with 92' of frontage on E. 7th, and a depth of 128') within the Plaza Saltillo Transit Oriented Development (TOD) Station Area Plan and designated a Corridor Mixed-Use Subdistrict, with a permitted building height up to 60’ and up to 45 living units/acre, w/no minimum living unit requirement. This subdistrict allows the widest variety of uses in the TOD and may be eligible for the Affordable Housing Density Bonus. Nestled at the corner of East 7th and San Marcos Streets in East Austin, this prime location provides unparalleled walkability to downtown's pulse, fostering resident appeal through cultural, commercial, and professional synergy. Within a mere 0.3 miles lies the electrifying Sixth Street entertainment district, teeming with live music venues and nightlife. A brisk 0.5-mile stroll reaches the majestic Texas State Capitol, a hub for government and events drawing statewide foot traffic. Just 0.6 miles away, the Austin Convention Center anchors major conferences and tourism. The historic Paramount Theatre, renowned for performances, sits 0.7 miles to the west, while the eclectic Red River Cultural District—home to indie music clubs—beckons only 0.2 miles east. Lady Bird Lake's scenic trails and kayak launches unfold 0.8 miles south, promoting outdoor lifestyle integration. The iconic Congress Avenue Bridge bat colony spectacle is a short 1.0-mile jaunt, and the prestigious University of Texas campus lies 1.2 miles north, ideal for student housing demand. Nearby, the Bullock Texas State History Museum (0.9 miles) and the elegant Driskill Hotel (0.7 miles) enhance cultural and hospitality adjacency. The TOD reduces automobile dependency, boosts ridership on Capital MetroRail by 20-40%, lowers household transportation costs by $3,000-4,000 annually, decreases emissions, and fosters inclusive, walkable communities with density bonuses for affordable housing—perfectly aligning with a 60-foot mixed-use build. Residents would enjoy mere steps (about 0.3 miles) to the Plaza Saltillo MetroRail station at E. 5th and Comal, enabling seamless commutes to downtown, Leander, or beyond via the Red Line. Currently, the Plaza Saltillo area thrives as a 11-acre mixed-use hub showcasing East Austin's Hispanic heritage through public art, a Mexican-style plaza, diverse retail, restaurants, offices, and over 800 apartments (including 18% affordable units for households up to 50% median family income), all interconnected by pedestrian paseos, bike shares, and sustainable features like LEED-certified buildings and native landscaping. Looking ahead, ongoing and future enhancements—guided by the 2009 Station Area Plan and recent 2025 regulating updates—promise expanded open spaces (1.4 acres of parks), extended bikeways linking to Lady Bird Lake, innovative stormwater management, and vibrant economic growth, solidifying it as a live-work-play epicenter that preserves cultural character while attracting creative professionals and bolstering long-term property value for developers. This positions the site as a prime canvas for high-density residential and retail vitality in Austin's thriving core. Additional parcel may be available to bring total square footage to 14,400 SF.

description: Premier Development Opportunity on .42 acre lot on the same block as ST DAVID'S SOUTH AUSTIN MEDICAL CENTER. The property is currently zoned Single Family - 3 - Neighborhood Planning (SF-3-NP). This property is located within the St. David's Hospital "Special District" making is prime for commercial redevelopment. See the South Austin Combined Neighborhood Planning Area Map and notice that this property is in Blue in Special District along James Casey Street. Will works on both industrial leasing and tenant representation assignments. He has his boots on the ground every day touring spaces and conducting lease transactions.

Will originally joined AQUILA as an intern before transitioning into a junior broker position. During his time at AQUILA. Will has gained vast knowledge of the Austin market by assisting both tenants and landlords in executing leases.

Will loves music, both playing it and listening. It’s part of what led him to stay in Austin, rather than return to his hometown of Houston.

brokerDetails.name: Leigh Ellis, SIOR
brokerDetails.tagLine: Specializes in Project Leasing, Tenant Representation, Industrial
brokerDetails.bio:
Leigh has played a crucial role in building AQUILA’s industrial platform. His client portfolio includes a diverse range of prominent institutional real estate owners nationwide such as Stonelake Capital, United Properties, Hines, Jackson Shaw, and Brookfield.

As a CoStar Power Broker and Austin Business Journal Heavy Hitter for several years, Leigh has solidified his position as one of Austin’s premier industrial leasing brokers. His work also earned him the No. 1 spot as an Austin Business Journal Heavy Hitter for Investment Sales in 2022. Outside of work, Leigh is a proud Texas Longhorn and an avid golfer.

brokerDetails.name: Jason Steinberg
brokerDetails.tagLine: Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects.
brokerDetails.bio:
Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects. Jason has provided leasing and sales services since 2008 and prior to joining ECR in 2010, Jason worked at a local commercial construction firm.

Jason has successfully completed more than 1,100 real estate deals totaling more than $1,000,000,000 in value. He is annually recognized as an Austin Business Journal “Heavy Hitter” and received the SIOR Designation in 2016.

Jason is involved with the Society of Industrial and Office Realtors (SIOR), the Commercial Brokers Association (CBA), Austin Diaper Bank, Sammy’s House, the Anti-Defamation League (ADL), and the Jewish Community Association of Austin.

Jason received a B.A. degree from The University of Texas at Austin. Jason and his wife, Allison, have two young children and live in Austin’s Northwest Hills neighborhood.

brokerDetails.name: Rebecca Zigterman
brokerDetails.tagLine: In addition to landlord representation, Rebecca represents tenants with their site selection, negotiation, and long-term strategy.
brokerDetails.bio:
Rebecca joined ECR as its third team member in 2010 and currently oversees project leasing responsibilities for over one million SF of office and medical space. In addition to landlord representation, Rebecca represents tenants with their site selection, negotiation, and long-term strategy while also providing commercial real estate sales services through client dispositions and acquisitions.  Rebecca has completed over 550 transactions and has been recognized as an Austin Business Journal “Heavy Hitter” for multiple years.

Rebecca is currently in her third year of serving on the Board of Directors for the Commercial Brokers Association (CBA) as the liaison to its two local charities, RMHC and Mainspring Schools.  She also helps lead ECR Serves and is involved with Gateway Church in Austin.

Prior to ECR, Rebecca worked at Stanford University in the residential and dining department. Prior to Stanford, Rebecca worked for RE/MAX Alliance in the greater Boulder area after graduating from the University of Colorado in Boulder (CU), where she received her Bachelor of Arts and a certificate of business and developed her passion for real estate.

brokerDetails.name: Brita Hovde
brokerDetails.tagLine: Senior Associate at Stream Realty Partners
brokerDetails.bio:
Brita Hovde serves as an associate on the agency leasing team in Austin. Her primary responsibilities include conducting critical research, project leasing, and evaluating trends in Austin’s office market. Brita is also involved in supporting Stream’s principal transactions. Prior to joining Stream, Brita worked for Ares Management as an Internal Sales Consultant in their wealth management division in Denver, CO. Brita graduated from the Leeds School of Business at the University of Colorado-Boulder in 2021 with an emphasis in Real Estate and a certificate in Entrepreneurship. Brita is a passionate advocate for an active and outdoorsy lifestyle, with a deep love for skiing, biking, swimming, and hiking adventures. When she’s not exploring the great outdoors, you can find her in the heart of the city, enjoying the vibrant energy of live music shows and concerts.

Stream Realty Partners is one of the fastest-growing full-service commercial real estate companies in the nation. We have more than 270M+ million square feet of office, industrial, retail, and healthcare assignments, resulting in over $5.8 billion in real estate transactions annually. 

Founded in 1996, Stream has grown from its two original partners to a staff of over 1,200+ real estate professionals who share one common goal: to provide an unequaled level of service to our clients. 

Graduated from the University of Colorado-Boulder in June 2021 with a bachelor degree in Business Administration with an emphasis in real estate and a certificate in entrepreneurship.

brokerDetails.name: Brad Philp
brokerDetails.tagLine: Brad is part of the Austin Office Team and is focused on growing the portfolio & team while providing best in class services to our clients.
brokerDetails.bio: Brad is a Managing Director & Partner at Stream Realty Partners.  Brad joined Stream in 2010 and his primary responsibilities include but are not limited to: leading Stream’s Office team, project leasing, tenant representation, and acquisition / disposition services.  Brad is part of the Austin Office Team and is focused on growing the portfolio and the team while providing best in class services to our clients. The Austin Business Journal has consistently designated Brad as a “Heavy Hitter”. Since joining Stream Brad has been involved in over 5,333,000 SF of executed Leases totaling over $1.1 billion in total consideration.  His clients include and have included: KBS, Heitman, CIM, USAA Real Co, AFIAA, Spear Street, MIG, Dividend Capital, HRPT (REIT Management & Research).   He has worked on transactions with some of the biggest names in Austin, including, but not limited to: Google, Oracle, Qualcomm, Under Armor, Dropbox, Athena Health Care, Citizens Inc,  Bank of America, and HomeAway.  Prior to joining Stream, Brad worked for Forestar Group Inc. (FOR) from 2005 – 2010. During his time at Forestar, Brad worked as a Financial Analyst and Development Associate where he focused on the acquisition, entitlement, and development of land development projects in various markets throughout the United States. ? Brad is actively involved in his community.?He is a member of the Real Estate Council of Austin (RECA) and the Commercial Brokers Association (CBA).?He currently serves as Board President of Travis County MUD #16 and was a past Board Member at Casner Christian Academy.  He’s involved in his local scouting troop as well as his kids sports. ? Brad is a graduate of TCU where he received a BBA in Finance as well as Texas A&M University where he received a Masters of Land Economics and Real Estate.?Brad is an Eagle Scout and loves all aspects of the outdoors.  Brad resides in Austin with his wife and three children.

brokerDetails.name: Jason Steinberg
brokerDetails.tagLine: Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects.
brokerDetails.bio:
Jason Steinberg specializes in representing businesses with new and existing office projects. Jason has provided leasing and sales services since 2008 and prior to joining ECR in 2010, Jason worked at a local commercial construction firm.

Jason has successfully completed more than 1,100 real estate deals totaling more than $1,000,000,000 in value. He is annually recognized as an Austin Business Journal “Heavy Hitter” and received the SIOR Designation in 2016.

Jason is involved with the Society of Industrial and Office Realtors (SIOR), the Commercial Brokers Association (CBA), Austin Diaper Bank, Sammy’s House, the Anti-Defamation League (ADL), and the Jewish Community Association of Austin.

Jason received a B.A. degree from The University of Texas at Austin. Jason and his wife, Allison, have two young children and live in Austin’s Northwest Hills neighborhood.

brokerDetails.name: Sean Couey
brokerDetails.tagLine: Sean is a Brokerage Advisor for ECR.
brokerDetails.bio:
Sean always takes his clients’ highest and best interests to heart and exceeding expectations is standard practice.

Sean possesses a unique set of skills developed in project management, marketing, and sales within companies ranging in size from start-up to multinational.  These diverse experiences are why Sean is quick to understand his clients’ positions and find optimal solutions for their businesses.

Sean is a graduate of UC San Diego with a BA in economics and has lived and worked in both Silicon Valley and NYC.  Sean brings a valuable perspective that allows him to better understand the quickly changing Austin market.

In his free time, Sean can be found searching for the best taco with his wife, son, and dog.

spaces.name: 1st Floor
spaces.description:
Discover a rare move-in-ready opportunity in the heart of Central Austin. 1708 W Koenig Ln is a 1,830 SF freestanding building that has been thoughtfully renovated with a high-end, retail-style finish-out designed for today’s modern businesses.

The space features glass-enclosed offices and conference areas, wood flooring, contemporary lighting, and a flexible open layout that creates a polished, professional, client-facing environment. Furniture is included, allowing a buyer or tenant to occupy the space immediately with minimal downtime or upfront expense. The layout is well-suited for creative office users, boutique retail, medical or wellness practices, design studios, or professional service businesses seeking a turnkey solution.

Positioned prominently along Koenig Lane, the property offers excellent visibility, steady traffic counts, on-site parking, and convenient access to North Lamar, Burnet Road, MoPac, and I-35. The flexible LO-MU-NP zoning supports a wide range of uses and adds long-term versatility for both owner-users and tenants.

This property is being offered For Sale or For Lease. Contact the listing agent for pricing, lease terms, and additional details, or to schedule a private tour.

An exceptional opportunity for a business seeking visibility, accessibility, functionality and flexibility in one of the most sought-after commercial corridors in North Austin. 9201 Metric Blvd offers a versatile, high-end move in-ready space ideal for office, warehouse, showroom, or mixed-use operations, perfect for a wide range of tenants or owner user. 

Property Overview 
• Total Building Size: 13,200 SF 
• Site Size: Just under 1 acre 
• Building Footprint: 90’ x 120’ (10,800 SF) 
• Mezzanine/Storage: 2,400 SF 
• Year Built: 1994 
• Availability: January 2026 

Key Features 
• Grade and dock-high loading on both sides of the building 
• Fully climate-controlled warehouse and office space 
• Two existing power meters (previously demised into two suites) 
• Open forklift-accessible connection between both sides 
• Flexible layout for one or two tenants 
• Ample on-site parking and fenced yard space with automatic gate 
• Excellent Visibility from Metric Blvd with building signage 
• Convenient access to major corridors, including US-183, IH-35, and MoPac 

Breakdown by Area 
• Warehouse: ±6,000 SF | 19’ Clear Height | Fully HVAC Controlled | 18 Standard Parking Spaces 
• Office Suite A: 2,400 SF

BEING OFFERED FOR SALE & FOR LEASE: 11104 N Lamar Blvd offers a rare covered land opportunity in North Austin, featuring approximately 17,000 SF of warehouse and showroom/retail space on 1.02 acres along one of the city’s busiest commercial corridors. The property is functional for warehouse, retail, or flex use while offering excellent long-term redevelopment potential. Centrally located between Braker Lane and Kramer Lane, the site provides outstanding visibility and quick access to IH-35, US-183, and The Domain. With strong demographics, high traffic counts, and flexible positioning options, it stands out as a prime opportunity for investors or owner-users in one of Austin’s most dynamic trade areas. lotDetails.description:
FOR LEASE – 1,332 SF End-Cap Flex Space | 2512 W Pecan St, Pflugerville, TX

Built in 2022 and recently refreshed, this well-equipped end-cap suite provides a modern, versatile setting ideal for showroom, office, light industrial, or service-oriented users. With high visibility, easy access, and a polished industrial appeal, 2512 W Pecan Street offers one of Pflugerville’s most attractive lease opportunities for growing businesses

End-Cap Exposure: Premium corner suite with excellent visibility along West Pecan Street, one of Pflugerville’s busiest commercial corridors.

Flexible Floor Plan: Approximately 1,330 SF featuring open workspace, private restroom, HVAC, water heater, and a ±400 SF mezzanine office. Perfect for light industrial, showroom, office, or service-based users.

Modern Industrial Appeal: High ceilings with a clean, contemporary finish, standard roll-up and glass entry doors, and signage opportunities on both the building and monument sign.

Convenient Access: Minutes from SH-130 and I-35 with ample on-site parking for staff and customers.
